  </div>

  <!-- FAQ Sections -->
  <div class="faq-sections">
    <!-- Getting Started -->
    <section id="getting-started" class="faq-section">
      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>How do I create an account?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Creating an account is easy! Click the "Sign Up" button in the top right corner, fill in your information including your name, email, school, and grade level, then verify your email address. Once verified, you can start exploring tutors and offering your own skills.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Is SkillSwap free to use?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes! SkillSwap is completely free for students. Our mission is to make peer-to-peer learning accessible to everyone.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>How do I become a tutor?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Any registered user can become a tutor! Go to your profile settings, switch to "Tutor" mode, and add the skills you'd like to teach. Make sure to include your experience level and any relevant achievements to attract students.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>What subjects can I learn or teach?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>SkillSwap supports a wide range of academic subjects including Math, Science, English, History, and Foreign Languages. You can also teach and learn skills like programming, music, art, and more. If you don't see your skill listed, you can add a custom skill tag.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Sessions -->
    <section id="sessions" class="faq-section">
      <h2>Sessions</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>How do I request a tutoring session?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Find a tutor through our Explore page, view their profile, and click "Request Session." Choose a skill, select your preferred date and time, and add a message explaining what you'd like to learn. The tutor will receive your request and can accept or suggest alternative times.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>What happens after a tutor accepts my request?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Once accepted, you'll receive a notification and the session will appear in your dashboard. You can message the tutor to discuss details, share materials, or confirm the meeting location (in-person or virtual).</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Can I cancel a session?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes, you can cancel a session, but we ask that you do so at least 24 hours in advance whenever possible. To cancel, go to your Sessions page and click "Cancel" on the relevant session. Please provide a reason to help the other person understand.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Where do tutoring sessions take place?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Sessions can be held in-person or online. For in-person sessions, we recommend meeting in public places like libraries or school common areas. For online sessions, you can use any video conferencing tool you're comfortable with.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Account -->
    <section id="account" class="faq-section">
      <h2>Account</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>How do I edit my profile?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Click on your avatar in the top right corner and select "Edit Profile." You can update your bio, skills, availability, and profile picture. Don't forget to save your changes!</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>How do I change my password?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Go to Settings > Security and click "Change Password." You'll need to enter your current password and then your new password twice to confirm.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Can I delete my account?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes, you can delete your account from Settings > Account > Delete Account. Please note that this action is permanent and will remove all your data, including session history and reviews.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Safety -->
    <section id="safety" class="faq-section">
      <h2>Safety</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>How does SkillSwap keep users safe?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Safety is our top priority. We verify student status during registration, have a review system to surface reliable tutors, maintain a reporting system for inappropriate behavior, and follow strict data privacy practices. We also provide safety guidelines for in-person meetings.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>How do I report inappropriate behavior?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>If you encounter any inappropriate behavior, please report it immediately. You can use the "Report" button on any user's profile or message thread. Our team reviews all reports within 24 hours and takes appropriate action.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>What information is visible to other users?</span>
            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Other users can see your first name, profile picture, bio, skills, grade level, and reviews. Your email, phone number, and specific school name are kept private unless you choose to share them.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <!-- Contact Support -->
  <div class="contact-support mt-6">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-body text-center">
        <h3>Still need help?</h3>
        <p>Our support team is here to assist you</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Support</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .help-search {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  .form-input-lg {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
  }
  
  .quick-links {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  
  .quick-link {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid var(--neutral-200);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--neutral-700);
    transition: var(--transition-fast);
  }
  
  .quick-link:hover {
    border-color: var(--primary-300);
    color: var(--primary-600);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }
  
  .quick-link-icon {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }
  
  .faq-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  
  .faq-section h2 {
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--primary-500);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  .faq-item {
    border: 1px solid var(--neutral-200);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  
  .faq-question {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: white;
    border: none;
    text-align: left;
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--neutral-800);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: var(--transition-fast);
  }
  
  .faq-question:hover {
    background: var(--neutral-50);
  }
  
  .faq-toggle {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--primary-500);
    transition: var(--transition-fast);
  }
  
  .faq-item.open .faq-toggle {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }
  
  .faq-answer {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.3s ease;
  }
  
  .faq-item.open .faq-answer {
    max-height: 500px;
  }
  
  .faq-answer p {
    padding: 0 1.25rem 1.25rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--neutral-600);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  
  .contact-support .card {
    max-width: 500px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
</style>

<script>
  // FAQ toggle
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-question').forEach(button => {
    button.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const item = button.parentElement;
      item.classList.toggle('open');
    });
  });
  
  // Search filter
  const helpSearch = document.getElementById('helpSearch');
  helpSearch?.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
    const query = e.target.value.toLowerCase();
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(item => {
      const text = item.textContent.toLowerCase();
      item.style.display = text.includes(query) ? 'block' : 'none';
    });
  });
  
  // Smooth scroll for anchor links
  document.querySelectorAll('a[href^="#"]').forEach(anchor => {
    anchor.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();
      const target = document.querySelector(anchor.getAttribute('href'));
      if (target) {
        target.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' });
      }
    });
  });
</script>
